ning a Jammed Lock 1 Push or pull the door as you turn the key.";i:42;s:31:"2 Turn the key both directions.";i:43;s:72:"Theres no universal standard for which way a key turns to unlock a door.";i:44;s:21:"3 Lubricate the lock.";i:45;s:19:"4 Examine the keys.";i:46;s:27:"5 Know when to apply force.";i:47;s:20:"6 Try other methods.";i:48;s:86:"Using the basic science of expansion and contraction cool the key to make it contract.";i:49;s:96:"Place one or two ice cubes in a plastic bag and hold it against the stuck key for a few minutes.";i:50;s:85:"This should cause the key to contract allowing its teeth to clear from the lock pins.";}}